                                         BLOEMFONTEIN - The National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) is appealing the High Courtâ€™s sentence of Oscar Pistorius, arguing that it is shockingly lenient for the crime of murder. The former athlete was sentenced to six years in prison for murdering his girlfriend Reeva Steenkamp. Pistorius shot and killed Steenkamp on Valentine's Day in 2013, claiming that he believed she was an intruder. WATCH: NPA appeals Oscar Pistorius sentence  It is the second time that the State is asking the Supreme Court to set aside a High Court decision in the trial of Pistorius. The State successfully overturned his culpable homicide conviction, replacing it with one of murder. 
